-- Niger's Abdoulaye Badie, Second in Command in Junta, Has Been Arrested
-- B y   D j i b r i l   S a i d o u
-- 2010-10-14T14:16:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/niger-s-abdoulaye-badie-second-in-command-in-junta-has-been-arrested.html
Colonel Abdoulaye Badie, the second
in comand in Niger’s military government, was arrested yesterday
and is being detained at the army’s headquarters, two military
officials with knowledge of the arrest said.  Badie served as permanent secretary of the Supreme Council
for the Restoration of Democracy, the name of the junta, until
Oct. 10 when General Djibo Salou abolished the post.  The officials declined to be identified because they aren’t
authorized to speak to the press.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  